      <hedline>
        <hl1>Seeing Genoa</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Gerald and Lillian Levin letter on Michael Frank's April 9 travel article notes excellent municipal bus tour of city (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: To the many pleasures Michael Frank describes in ''Genoa, City of Contrasts (April 9) should be added the funiculars to spectacular views from high points. The excellent municipal bus tour of the city, originating at the train station, can be joined at various marked stops.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: To the many pleasures Michael Frank describes in ''Genoa, City of Contrasts (April 9) should be added the funiculars to spectacular views from high points. The excellent municipal bus tour of the city, originating at the train station, can be joined at various marked stops.</p>
        <p>The three galleries mentioned contain one of the most extensive art collections in northern Italy -- the Palazzo Spinola, the national gallery in the historic center, has a magnificent Antonello, in addition to fine works by Van Dyck, Rubens, Guercino, Strozzi and Reni. The Academy of Fine Arts was closed when we visited, but the rebuilt opera house is open again. As Mr. Frank notes, a week would not exhaust this beautiful, hospitable city.</p>
        <p>GERALD LEVIN  LILLIAN LEVIN  Glastonbury, Conn.</p>
      </block>
